==English==
===Adjective===
'''plumper'''

#[[Comparative]] of '''[[plump]]'''.

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

#One who [[plump]]s or [[swell]]s out something else
#That which [[plump]]s or [[swell]]s out something else
#Hence, something carried in the mouth to [[distend]] the cheeks.
#In English [[election]]s, a [[vote]] given to one [[candidate]] only, when two or more are to be elected, thus giving him the [[advantage]] over the others; a person who gives his vote thus is said to plump, or to plump his vote.
#A voter who plumps his vote.
#A [[downright]], [[unqualified]] [[lie]].

